data.content:
These are two separate issues:

## 1. `left && right` — dynamic + interface `operator true/false`

The `&&` operator desugars into calls to `operator true` and `operator &`. With `dynamic` on the right, the runtime binder must resolve `operator true`/`operator false` on the left operand's type. In C# 15, the compiler now **rejects this at compile time** when the left operand is an **interface type** (`IFilter`), because the dynamic binder cannot dispatch to static operators defined on interfaces.

**Fix:** avoid mixing `dynamic` with interface-typed short-circuit operators:

```csharp
void Apply(IFilter left, dynamic right)
{
    // Option A: cast to concrete type
    var combined = (CompositeFilter)left && right;

    // Option B: desugar manually
    var combined = IFilter.op_True(left) ? left : left & (IFilter)right;
}
```

## 2. `ref readonly` lambda return — CS0518

CS0518 ("Predefined type is not defined or imported") means the compiler needs a BCL attribute type (e.g. `RequiresLocationAttribute`) to encode the `ref readonly` return in metadata, but your target framework doesn't include it.

This is a **TFM mismatch** — you have the C# 15 compiler but aren't targeting `net11.0`. Check your project file:

```xml
<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>
```

Make sure your SDK is the .NET 11 SDK (not just the C# 15 language version forced onto an older runtime).
